* [[Bruce Perens]] (April 1996 – December 1997)
* [[Ian Jackson]] (January 1998 – December 1998)
* [[Wichert Akkerman]] (January 1999 – March 2001)
* [[Ben Collins (programmer)|Ben Collins]] (April 2001 – April 2002)
* [[Bdale Garbee]] (April 2002 – April 2003)
* [[Martin Michlmayr]] (March 2003 – March 2005)
* [[Branden Robinson]] (April 2005 – April 2006)
* [[Anthony Towns]] (April 2006 – April 2007)
* [[Sam Hocevar]] (April 2007 – April 2008)
* [[Steve McIntyre]] (April 2008 – April 2010)
* [[Stefano Zacchiroli]] (April 2010 – April 2013)
* [[Lucas Nussbaum]] (April 2013 – present)<ref>{{cite web
| url =https://lists.debian.org/debian-vote/2013/04/msg00027.html
| author =Devotee
| date =April 13, 2013
| title =Results for Debian Project Leader 2013 Election
}}</ref>

A supplemental position, ''Debian Second in Charge'' (2IC), was created by Anthony Towns. [[Steve McIntyre]] held the position between April 2006 and April 2007. From April 2009 to April 2010 this position was held by Luk Claes. Stefano Zacchiroli abandoned this unofficial position when elected in April 2010.<ref>{{cite web |url =http://www.debian.org/vote/2010/platforms/zack |at=section 2.2.3 No DPL board |title =DPL Platform&nbsp;— Stefano Zacchiroli |date =2010-03-12 |publisher =Debian |quote=I do not believe in the utility of a DPL board, so I will not have one; nor I will have a second in charge (2IC).}}</ref>

